  "suggestion": "The plateau is likely caused by a **morphological ceiling**: current organism design space (likely simple cell grids or blobs) can only express so many viable phenotypes before all variations hit diminishing returns on the fitness function. The system optimizes within a constrained solution space rather than opening new ones. Breaking through requires increasing the *expressive capacity* of the genome (specialization → more degrees of freedom) or the *selection pressure environment* (dynamics/competition → higher peaks worth evolving toward). Parameter tuning within the current architecture is exhausted.; [hard] Introduce cell type specialization: sensor cells (detect environment), actuator cells (movement/growth), metabolic cells (energy conversion), structural cells (form/rigidity). Organisms must use multiple types; beauty includes morphological complexity metrics. — Homogeneous organisms have flat fitness gradients. Specialization opens a vast new morphospace where body-plan diversity becomes directly selectable. Organisms evolve tissue differentiation strategies, enabling completely new body architectures that current simple designs cannot explore. Breaks plateau by adding ~100x more degrees of freedom.; [medium] Add environmental cycles: periodic resource redistribution (food patches move every N cycles), temperature/light gradients that shift, seasonal bottlenecks where survival is harder. World state becomes non-stationary. — Static environments converge to local optima fast. Cycling conditions force organisms to either: (a) become generalists that survive all phases, or (b) specialize and handle only part of the cycle—both paths create new selection pressures. Prevents fitness plateau by making the landscape itself dynamic. Beauty can now reward adaptability.; [hard] Implement pheromone/chemical signaling layer: organisms can emit signals that persist in the world and influence neighbor behavior. Enable cooperation mechanics (quorum sensing, collective growth decisions). Beauty scoring rewards coordinated group behavior patterns. — Current organisms are isolated agents optimizing individual traits. Signaling enables emergent collective intelligence and cooperation strategies—a new interaction dimension that individual-level selection alone cannot discover. Plateau suggests individual optimization is saturated; collective behavior is orthogonal and unexplored. Compounds with specialization above.",
